another wedding, I was present, he, our friend was the
groom, I was present at that wedding.

373
00:29:03,000 --> 00:29:06,000
Dengbêjek li ser mesrehê sikinî bû,
 
A singer was standing on the stage,

374
00:29:06,000 --> 00:29:10,000
Yanî min va tasarufata gî da nêrinê... min got, vo nesax e.
 
I mean all these behaviors in view... I said, this is
inappropriate.

375
00:29:10,000 --> 00:29:15,000
Kese kê be... bes carna çêdibe, yanî em kênebêjin, çi
dibe...
 
Whoever it may be... but sometimes it happens, I mean let's
say, what happens...

376
00:29:15,000 --> 00:29:20,000
we tiştan jî heye... kekê welat jî hazir dibe kekê Alî... em
gî hazir dibin...
 
these things happen too... brother Welat is also present
brother Alî... we are all present...

377
00:29:20,000 --> 00:29:25,000
Dengbêjekî kêma meşrû be wexê herî lê dawetê hazir be.
Nêrînê te ji vî tiştî da çî ye?
 
A singer acting less than legitimate when going to be
present at a wedding. What is your view on this?

378
00:29:25,000 --> 00:29:28,000
Mamoste, dijminê yekî,
 
Master, a person's first enemy,

379
00:29:28,000 --> 00:29:31,000
ji deng ra... elmiyen, ti...
 
to the voice... scientifically, you...

380
00:29:31,000 --> 00:29:36,000
Na bes, meşrûbe teqetke, na bes, gotinê min nese be,
dengbêjo be'zem em kînebe tembûrcî jî wa te ke.
 
No, but, drinking legitimate drinks, no, but, what I'm
saying might not be right, singers sometimes let's say a saz
player acts like that too.

381
00:29:36,000 --> 00:29:38,000
Na. Na. Arîfî heflê jî wa te ke.
 
No. No. The party MC acts like that too.

382
00:29:38,000 --> 00:29:43,000
Erê, dijminê yeke ji deng ra hew tişta yanî, me elesef vî
tiştan jê mewcûde heye yanî.
 
Yes, the first enemy to the voice is that thing I mean,
unfortunately these things exist I mean.

383
00:29:43,000 --> 00:29:46,000
Tiştikî pir şaşe. Yanî herro da'weta xelke.
 
It's a very wrong thing. I mean today is people's wedding.

384
00:29:46,000 --> 00:29:50,000
Tê hatî... xelke qosîre xwe ke tu pere xwe dibe ye heçiz
biye.
 
You came... people try their best you take your money it's
booked.

385
00:29:50,000 --> 00:29:51,000
Temam?
 
Right?

386
00:29:51,000 --> 00:29:54,000
Te key waxwe isikasi p'itê t'ene.
 
You don't have the right to act like that.

387
00:29:54,000 --> 00:29:58,000
Te kone here male xa waxwe. Te kone herre qawengik xa... ma
t'ame kixarine... waxe e isikasi p'te t'ene.
 
You can go to your own house to do that. You can go to a
café... eat a meal... you don't have the right to act like
that.

388
00:29:58,000 --> 00:30:00,000
Emma dawete...
 
But at a wedding...

389
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:02,000
Xelkê, bi dawetên xelkê
 
People, at people's weddings

390
00:30:02,000 --> 00:30:06,000
Yanî ne şert e tu wek, bi Efrînkî dibêjin, "tê ser xweş
wara" dawetên xelkê...
 
I mean, it's not a condition that you, as they say in
Afrini, "tê ser xweş wara" (you come as a guest) to people's
weddings...

391
00:30:06,000 --> 00:30:08,000
Erê. Bêje, bêje, bêje.
 
Yes. Say it, say it, say it.

392
00:30:08,000 --> 00:30:10,000
Yanî, tiştekî pir xweş e.
 
I mean, it's a very nice thing.

393
00:30:10,000 --> 00:30:11,000
Xweş e.
 
It's nice.

394
00:30:11,000 --> 00:30:13,000
Yanî tiştekî ne kok e, ne cuda ye... ne loiq e...
 
I mean, it's not something out of place, not different...
not inappropriate...

395
00:30:13,000 --> 00:30:16,000
Fenî, ku biqasî bibînin hunermendê Efrînê rabike.
 
Artistic, so that they can see an Afrini artist rise.

396
00:30:16,000 --> 00:30:19,000
Qisê te re ewqas, huro ez li ser mesrehê bisekinim, em bi
Efrînkî, bi mişermehî deng kin.
 
To cut your story short, today if I stand on the stage,
let's talk in Afrini, openly.

397
00:30:19,000 --> 00:30:20,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

398
00:30:20,000 --> 00:30:24,000
Ez li ser mesrehê bisekinim, bavêkî zêva tê cem min,
carna...
 
If I stand on the stage, a father of the groom comes to me,
sometimes...

399
00:30:24,000 --> 00:30:25,000
Di nav civatê.
 
In front of the gathering.

400
00:30:25,000 --> 00:30:29,000
Ew dibêje ji min re "bavêkî zêva", yê ku bibêje "min mutrib
eciz kirîye, yan min yêkî dawetê me wexandiye, min eciz
kirîye"...
 
He says to me, "the father of the groom", the one who says
"I have upset the singer, or I have invited someone to the
wedding and upset them"...

401
00:30:29,000 --> 00:30:32,000
...yên vê tiştî nabêje da.
 
...nobody says this.

402
00:30:32,000 --> 00:30:34,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

403
00:30:34,000 --> 00:30:38,000
Qisê te re ewqas, yanî bavêkî zêva yê ku bibêje dawetê wî
birokî min...
 
To cut your story short, I mean, the father of the groom who
says "his wedding has hit me"...

404
00:30:38,000 --> 00:30:44,000
...ew dawetê birokî, yanî lê wi qasê dayîn, kî ye? Fulan e,
jimara min e dawetê.
 
...that wedding hit him, meaning it cost him that much, who
is it? It's so-and-so, it's my number at the wedding.

405
00:30:44,000 --> 00:30:46,000
Carik din, mafê xwe te daye, tu kêfa xwe bînî.
 
Once again, he has given you your right, you enjoy yourself.

406
00:30:46,000 --> 00:30:48,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

407
00:30:48,000 --> 00:30:52,000
Her înson e ku ser xwe radibe ser xwe derdixîne, gihîştî ye
dijînê mecalê xwe.
 
Every person who rises up and expresses themselves, has
reached it living in their own environment.

408
00:30:52,000 --> 00:30:56,000
Mesele, ser dawetan da yên kir... em derbasî ser çend
sitranên bi navê te hene.
 
For example, the ones who performed at weddings... let's
move on to how many songs you have to your name.

409
00:30:56,000 --> 00:30:58,000
Erê.
 
Yes.

410
00:30:58,000 --> 00:31:03,000
Û gotinek hene?
 
And are there any lyrics?

411
00:31:03,000 --> 00:31:06,000
Bi Xwedê mamoste, wek te zanîye yanî...
 
By God, teacher, as you know, I mean...

412
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:08,000
Di çi salê te dest pê kirîye?
 
In what year did you start?

413
00:31:08,000 --> 00:31:12,000
Ji 2020'an da min dest pê kirîye. Ez êdî bi hiciz bûm.
 
I started from 2020. I was already booked.

414
00:31:12,000 --> 00:31:16,000
Zovakî min re deng kir, got, "were dawetê min." Ez derketim.
 
A groom called me, he said, "come to my wedding." I went
out.

415
00:31:16,000 --> 00:31:21,000
Ê min xwest, nika gilî... mamoste, nika cem me wek em zanin,
xebreta min, mutewadi'...
 
And I wanted, now the words... teacher, now among us, as we
know, my modest experience...

416
00:31:21,000 --> 00:31:24,000
...ekademî heye û şe'bî heye.
 
...there is academic and there is popular (folk).

417
00:31:24,000 --> 00:31:29,000
Ê me nexwest... min îxtîyara min, ez ketim el-fenn el-şe'bî.
 
And we didn't want... my choice, I got into popular art.

418
00:31:29,000 --> 00:31:34,000
El-fenn el-şe'bî, yanî dawetên xelkê şahîyên xelkê, em hazir
dibin.
 
Popular art, I mean, people's weddings, people's
celebrations, we attend.

419
00:31:34,000 --> 00:31:37,000
Em baş ê ekademî jî heye. Yanî ekademî jî heye.
 
Well, there's also the academic part. I mean, there's also
the academic part.

420
00:31:37,000 --> 00:31:41,000
Mhmm.
 
Mhmm.

421
00:31:41,000 --> 00:31:46,000
Di qisimê me, em xwa em şe'bî ne, em muxenî, mutrib ev
fannon ev çi di mussema ye, em şe'bî nin tê hesib.
 
In our section, we ourselves are popular, we are singers,
mutribs, this artist, whatever the name is, we are
considered popular.

422
00:31:46,000 --> 00:31:47,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

423
00:31:47,000 --> 00:31:53,000
Min sitran ji îmkonyetê me... îmkonîyet ket-tescîl, ke
qudre...
 
I sang songs from our capabilities... capability as in
recording, as in power...

424
00:31:53,000 --> 00:31:57,000
...wê çaxê da tune bî. Nika jî tine ye bes... çê dibe, ya
waş ya waş jê pêş dikeve.
 
...at that time there wasn't any. Even now there isn't much,
but... it happens, it slowly progresses.

425
00:31:57,000 --> 00:31:59,000
Însan xwe pêş dixe.
 
A person develops themselves.

426
00:31:59,000 --> 00:32:04,000
Îmkonyete çi mamoste, e tescîl e, e bibêje meselen ke te kî
teswîr ke, ew ji ya te me pir divê.
 
What capabilities, teacher? It's recording, let's say for
example if you want to film, that requires a lot from you.

427
00:32:04,000 --> 00:32:08,000
Dilo, kî...
 
Dilo, who...

428
00:32:08,000 --> 00:32:11,000
Ê tu Efrînî, tu me'na zane, ne divê ez çi...
 
You are an Afrini, you know the meaning, I don't need to...

429
00:32:11,000 --> 00:32:15,000
Min eziyeta pir dî ser vê tiştî yanî. Ê nabe, el-heyat beda
testemir wekî dibêjin.
 
I suffered a lot for this thing, I mean. Well, it can't be
helped, life must go on, as they say.

430
00:32:15,000 --> 00:32:16,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

431
00:32:16,000 --> 00:32:22,000
Min sitranek çêkir, Evîndar im, Evîndar im, heqê xwe nebir.
 
I made a song, "Evîndar im, Evîndar im" (I am in love, I am
in love), it didn't get its due.

432
00:32:22,000 --> 00:32:23,000
Mhmm.
 
Mhmm.

433
00:32:23,000 --> 00:32:27,000
Jiber cuhda min betescîl kirî wê zemonî wê fetrê da hew
hebî.
 
Because the quality I recorded it with at that time, in that
period, was just that.

434
00:32:27,000 --> 00:32:28,000
Gotin ê kê bîn, stîrana te bî?
 
Whose words were they, was it your song?

435
00:32:28,000 --> 00:32:34,000
Gotin ê min bîn, ji xwa ra, min ew kir yanî, Evîndar im,
Evîndar im, ji bo çavê te wanekî...
 
The words were mine, for myself, I made it, I mean, "I am in
love, I am in love, for those eyes of yours..."

436
00:32:34,000 --> 00:32:35,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

437
00:32:35,000 --> 00:32:40,000
Ê pir ew nebî. Di pey wê ra, di pey wê ra, min xwest ez...
 
It didn't become very popular. After that, after that, I
wanted to...

438
00:32:40,000 --> 00:32:41,000
...ez mu'esir bim.
 
...I wanted to be influential.

439
00:32:41,000 --> 00:32:43,000
Tu hê ji vî pirtir...
 
You wanted to be more than this...

440
00:32:43,000 --> 00:32:46,000
Ez mu'esir bim, erê. Ez mu'esir bim.
 
I wanted to be influential, yes. I wanted to be influential.

441
00:32:46,000 --> 00:32:49,000
Qisê te re ewqas zovakî yekî te heciz kirê, yekî gulten e.
 
To cut your story short, a groom booked you, he said
something.

442
00:32:49,000 --> 00:32:50,000
Çend sitranên te hebin?
 
How many songs do you have?

443
00:32:50,000 --> 00:32:53,000
Çend sitranê yekî hebin e, yekî gul tê ne.
 
How many songs someone has, one has a rose for them.

444
00:32:53,000 --> 00:32:55,000
Min sitranê zeytûnê çêkir.
 
I made the olive song.

445
00:32:55,000 --> 00:32:59,000
Sitranê zeytûnê... wek klîb hat...
 
The olive song... it came as a clip...

446
00:32:59,000 --> 00:33:00,000
Keşandin û derket.
 
Filmed and released.

447
00:33:00,000 --> 00:33:02,000
Erê.
 
Yes.

448
00:33:02,000 --> 00:33:07,000
Fikrî klîbê ek hebî u te we kir ku ruhekî turosî di nav kurî
xwe kir?
 
Was there a clip idea and you did it so that you put a
heritage spirit into your work?

449
00:33:07,000 --> 00:33:13,000
Û em kêne min jî yek ez, ez girtê vê sitranê zeytûnê dîn im.
 
And can we say that I am one, I am captivated by this olive
song.

450
00:33:13,000 --> 00:33:14,000
Erê.
 
Yes.

451
00:33:14,000 --> 00:33:19,000
Gotin... li ser Efrînê me ye, li ser bav û kalê me ye...
heta di gotinê da jî heye: "Darê zeytûnê li bend da..."
 
Words... it's about our Afrin, it's about our ancestors...
even in the words it says: "The olive tree is waiting..."

452
00:33:19,000 --> 00:33:22,000
"...kal û pîr e."
 
"...the old man and woman."

453
00:33:22,000 --> 00:33:23,000
Mhmm.
 
Mhmm.

454
00:33:23,000 --> 00:33:28,000
Kelîmat - gotin ê kê bîn? Û tecsîl li kîderê bî? Û kesê te
re hazir kirîye, te çû ez daxwazim te çû...
 
Words - whose words were they? And where was it recorded?
And the person who prepared it for you, you went, I want you
to tell us...

455
00:33:28,000 --> 00:33:32,000
...rû ka vê klîbê ji me ra xeber de.
 
...give us the details of this clip.

456
00:33:32,000 --> 00:33:37,000
Silav û rêzê min... ji mamoste Mehdîn Mihemed ra hene.
Mehdînê Me'milo tê naskirin.
 
My greetings and respects... to teacher Mehdin Muhammed. He
is known as Mehdin of the Ma'milo family.

457
00:33:37,000 --> 00:33:38,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

458
00:33:38,000 --> 00:33:42,000
Kelîmat ê mamoste Mehdîn Mihemed in. Mehdînê Me'milo, silav
û rêz ji gundê wî ra tê.
 
The words are by teacher Mehdin Muhammed. Mehdin of Ma'milo,
greetings and respects go to his village.

459
00:33:42,000 --> 00:33:43,000
El-hon...
 
The melodies...

460
00:33:43,000 --> 00:33:46,000
Birokî me Welat Hec Nosir.
 
Our brother Welat Hec Nosir.

461
00:33:46,000 --> 00:33:47,000
Erê.
 
Yes.

462
00:33:47,000 --> 00:33:52,000
Girêdayî turos e, girêdayî mentîqê ye... el-hon, yanî ê
Welat Hec Nosir in.
 
It's connected to heritage, it's connected to the region...
the melodies, I mean, are Welat Hec Nosir's.

463
00:33:52,000 --> 00:33:53,000
Tescîl...
 
Recording...

464
00:33:53,000 --> 00:33:57,000
U silav û rêzê min... teb'en ji mamoste Xelîl Xilo ra jî
hene.
 
And my greetings and respects... of course to teacher Xelil
Xilo as well.

465
00:33:57,000 --> 00:34:00,000
Xelîl Xilo, yanî...
 
Xelil Xilo, I mean...

466
00:34:00,000 --> 00:34:04,000
Me di wextê klîb da hazir bî, silav û hurmet ji Xelîl Xilo
re jî...
 
We were present at the time of the clip, greetings and
respect to Xelil Xilo too...

467
00:34:04,000 --> 00:34:08,000
Mamoste me ye, hew jî bi me re hazir bî. Silav û rêz ji
gundê wî ra jî.
 
He is our teacher, he was also present with us. Greetings
and respects to his village too.

468
00:34:08,000 --> 00:34:12,000
Tescîl jî me li "Stüdyo Awaz" tescîl kir. Hew jî cem Xelîl
Xilo ye.
 
We also recorded at "Stüdyo Awaz". That is also with Xelil
Xilo.

469
00:34:12,000 --> 00:34:13,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

470
00:34:13,000 --> 00:34:18,000
Erê, me tescîl kir. Me hunî ev... me ser zeytûnê me çêkir.
 
Yes, we recorded it. We... we made it about the olive.

471
00:34:18,000 --> 00:34:22,000
Û silav û rêz dîsa ez dişînim... ji kekê Şîyar ra.
 
And again, I send greetings and respect... to brother Şîyar.

472
00:34:22,000 --> 00:34:24,000
Kekê Şîyar, yanî bavê Ciwan.
 
Brother Şîyar, meaning Ciwan's father.

473
00:34:24,000 --> 00:34:26,000
Her demê te xwa min ra xeber da...
 
Every time you spoke to me about him...

474
00:34:26,000 --> 00:34:28,000
Li her demekê, ew yek e... tiştekî girêdayî turos be...
 
At any time, he is the one... if it's something connected to
heritage...

475
00:34:28,000 --> 00:34:29,000
...îlla yekê basma wî xwa lê ketiye.
 
...he definitely left his mark on it.

476
00:34:29,000 --> 00:34:31,000
...jê hez dike.
 
...he loves it.

477
00:34:31,000 --> 00:34:35,000
Xewa, yanî çi tiştê girêdayî Efrînê be, tiştê girêdayî turos
be, yanî eşq dideyê.
 
Honestly, I mean, anything connected to Afrin, anything
connected to heritage, I mean, he puts passion into it.

478
00:34:35,000 --> 00:34:38,000
Silav û rêzê me ji kekê Şîyar ra hene yanî bavê Ciwan, silav
û rêz.
 
Our greetings and respects are to brother Şîyar, meaning
Ciwan's father, greetings and respects.

479
00:34:38,000 --> 00:34:41,000
Piştî te klîbek xwa sekinand û te daxist, te pey hesî heqê
xwa bir yan nebir?
 
After you finished your clip and released it, did you feel
it got its due or not?

480
00:34:41,000 --> 00:34:45,000
Heqê xwa yanî gor ke gotinê xwab Efrînî ne...
 
Its due, I mean, since its lyrics are in Afrini...

481
00:34:45,000 --> 00:34:47,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

482
00:34:47,000 --> 00:34:52,000
Yanî tu dikaribê bibê, "60% heqê xwab bir, û ne bir," yanî.
 
I mean, you could say, "it got 60% of its due, and it
didn't," I mean.

483
00:34:52,000 --> 00:34:54,000
Jiber çi? Jiber gotinê xwa bi Efrînî ne.
 
Why? Because its lyrics are in Afrini.

484
00:34:54,000 --> 00:34:55,000
Efrînî ye.
 
It's Afrini.

485
00:34:55,000 --> 00:34:59,000
Yanî menteqeya te yek e, girê nedî...
 
I mean, your region is one, it's not connected...

486
00:34:59,000 --> 00:35:04,000
Û ez sipasiyê min jî ji Vîdiyo Mîdya ra hene. Muxricê me...
 
And I also have my thanks to Video Media. Our director...

487
00:35:04,000 --> 00:35:07,000
Birokê min e yanî, em hev re ev dît û tiwalet ne jî yanî.
 
He is my brother, I mean, we grew up together, he's like a
childhood friend.

488
00:35:07,000 --> 00:35:08,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

489
00:35:08,000 --> 00:35:12,000
Hesen Celhût, silav û rêzê min ji kekê Hesen re jî hene.
 
Hesen Celhut, my greetings and respects to brother Hesen as
well.

490
00:35:12,000 --> 00:35:14,000
Wî jî teqsîr nekir bi me ra... Yanî kesekî bi me re teqsîr
nekir, serehe.
 
He didn't fall short with us either... I mean, no one fell
short with us, honestly.

491
00:35:14,000 --> 00:35:20,000
Kekê Hîm, wek ez zanim û her kes zane, Hîm sirrek li cem
gundiyan heye.
 
Brother Him, as I know and everyone knows, Him has a secret
among the villagers.

492
00:35:20,000 --> 00:35:23,000
Em ketin dengê min di Efrînê da...
 
I fell in love with my voice in Afrin...

493
00:35:23,000 --> 00:35:26,000
Xilafê sitranê gundan belav bîn, bi Erebî.
 
Apart from the village songs spreading, in Arabic.

494
00:35:26,000 --> 00:35:28,000
Te kî zimanê te heye bi Erebî distîrê?
 
Do you have a language where you sing in Arabic?

495
00:35:28,000 --> 00:35:32,000
Bi xwedê tu warê, tu warê barê...
 
By God, if you come, if you come to the burden...

496
00:35:32,000 --> 00:35:38,000
Niha tu warê barê, pir hunermendê me hene, dil û nexwe
distirên.
 
Now if you come to the burden, we have many artists, they
sing with all their heart and soul.

497
00:35:38,000 --> 00:35:41,000
Erebî jî distirên, û hunermendê me hene, Tirkî jî distirên.
 
They also sing Arabic, and we have artists who also sing
Turkish.

498
00:35:41,000 --> 00:35:42,000
Û yanî, evê huner e, eşê xuş tiştî tune ye.
 
And I mean, this is art, there is nothing bad about it.

499
00:35:42,000 --> 00:35:44,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

500
00:35:44,000 --> 00:35:48,000
Ehem, ehem tiştî... e sahbe...
 
The most important, the most important thing... is that it's
right...

501
00:35:48,000 --> 00:35:51,000
Tu warê meseleya huro ez kî Tirkî bistirêm, ez rêxî vê, ez
heqê wê tiştî pey dimê.
 
If you come to the issue, today if I want to sing in
Turkish, I arrange it, I give that thing its due.

502
00:35:51,000 --> 00:35:56,000
